Find $2^{-1} \pmod{185}$, as a residue modulo 185.  (Give an answer between 0 and 184, inclusive.)
inference: We seek an integer $x$ such that $2x \equiv 1 \pmod{185}$.  We can use the Extended Euclidean Algorithm to find such an $x$.  We have  \[185 = 92 \cdot 2 + 1.\]Then $1 = 185 - 92 \cdot 2$, so $2^{-1} \equiv \boxed{92} \pmod{185}$.  Final Answer: $\boxed{92}$. I hope it is correct.
